      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 425074506,
      "version": 803,
      "versionNonce": 976573114,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1784841881163,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Conclusion (assuming scripts are correct)\nFrom ALL 2 card hands, these are the max different outcomes for each decision\nHit: 4,717\nStand: 55\nDouble: 550\nSurrender: 55\nSplit: 17,576\n\nEven if these are wrong, the fact that we are getting them to a more than\nreasonable number is something I am happy about. Originally the goal was to\nkeep total simulations under 10 billion, maybe 1 billion for support for all\ndevices, so this feels unreal. Can't wait to see how the actual engine goes.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Conclusion (assuming scripts are correct)\nFrom ALL 2 card hands, these are the max different outcomes for each decision\nHit: 4,717\nStand: 55\nDouble: 550\nSurrender: 55\nSplit: 17,576\n\nEven if these are wrong, the fact that we are getting them to a more than\nreasonable number is something I am happy about. Originally the goal was to\nkeep total simulations under 10 billion, maybe 1 billion for support for all\ndevices, so this feels unreal. Can't wait to see how the actual engine goes.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
